args:
One day, a mysterious man named Aldred
suddenly attacks the prince. He fights back by
shapeshifting, but Aldred responds with a
shapeshift of his own! However, he is unable
to control the dragon's power and goes berserk,
after which the prince and his allies pursue him.
The reports said there were a large\nnumber of fiends amassing here,\nbut this is something else entirely.
Dude, the whole village is just...gone.
It seems their vast numbers\nwere no exaggeration.
Come on, everyone! It's time to\ntake these fiends out for good!
Sweet creepin' hell, they just keep comin'!\nFine then—see how ya like THIS!
Enough of this. It's time to shapeshift!\nO dragon, lend me your power!
Get 'em? You wiped the floor with 'em!

Still, this is no time for celebration;
I cannot imagine fiends gathering in
such numbers without some manner
of outside stimulus compelling them.
This whole thing stinks to high heaven,\nand I wanna know who's responsible!
A shapeshifter, is it? I guess the Syndicate\nfinally managed to create the perfect\nspecimen they were searching for.
Don't start getting high and mighty\njust because you managed to sweep\naside a few scrawny fiends.
What do you know about this?
Spill it, rando! Was this all your doing?!
If you are responsible for this,\nyou'll have to answer for it.
How rich that you speak of my answering\nfor crimes when it is YOU who should\nbe begging forgiveness from ME!
Uh, boss? I don't want to get all technical,\nbut it looks like this here cat's got a\ndragon...arm...thingie goin' on.
Burn the sight of it into your mind!\nLet it be etched onto your very souls!\nThis curse—MY curse—will be your end!
Hold on, Your Highness! We're coming!
Back off, peons! This is not your fight!
Holy hell! That dragon arm thingie's\ngot a punch like a runaway wagon!
All of you, stand down!\nLeave this to me!
Bold words—too bad they'll be your LAST!
If fighting is the only way you'll listen,\nI guess I'll just have to speak to you\nin a language you understand!
Then do it, if you can!
Dude, watch yourself out there!\nThis guy is the real deal!
Then I'll have to try a different approach...\nLend me your strength, O dragon!
Ha! You ain't the only one around here\nwho can control a dragon!
O dragon that burns inside me,\nGIVE ME YOUR POOOOOWER!
Oh, we're not done... I want more...\nGive me MOOOORE!
Stop! Your body can't take any more!
Quiet, Andromeda! My body is a small\nprice to pay if it means my revenge!
I'll wipe you from my sight,\nand then from the world itself!
I didn't expect to find myself fighting a\nshapeshifter here...
But even if you CAN shapeshift,\nI won't be defeated!
I will break you! Crush you! End you!\nI will grind your bones to dust and\nthen blow the dust into the WIIIIIND!
He's strong enough to fight the prince on\nequal terms... This is incredible...
This is not the time for marveling with\nyour jaw agape, Luca! We must help him!
Hang on! Something's happening\nto angry dragon guy!
He's mowin' down everything in sight!\nTrees! Buildings! BIGGER buildings!
It's almost as if he is not\nin control of his own power.
Oh, I KNEW this would happen...\nThe dragon's power is out of control!
I have to do something or else he'll...
Uh, wow. Okay. Looks like he took off.
Nothin' a hot bath and a roll of bandages\nwon't fix. Bigger question is, who in the\nname'a hell WAS that guy?
I don't know, but I don't think he's\nrelated to anyone of my bloodline.
Wait, can it be? Are you a member\nof the Alberian royal family?!
He sure is! ...Also, wait a sec.\nYou're that dragon from earlier!
Yes. My name is Andromeda,\nand I need your help. Please!
Help me save that man—\nhelp me save Aldred!
And how would you like us\nto do such a thing, exactly?

He has doubtlessly collapsed somewhere,
drained of energy after his rampage.
If a fiend or other enemy comes along,
he'll be at their mercy!
Did you miss the part where this guy\nwent bonkers and attacked us?\nWhy would we help him?!
I know how absurd it sounds, but you\nmust trust me when I tell you this is\nall just a...very large misunderstanding.
I don't have time to explain everything.\nPlease help me! I beg you!
Whether we want to help him or not,\nwe can't leave a violent man like that\nto wreak who-knows-what kind of havoc.
Also, if we can find him, it might help\nus understand why so many fiends\nsuddenly appeared in this place earlier.
All right, I think we have a plan.\nLet's go, everyone!
